casebody.data:
Mathis v. Weaver, executor. , while an interlocutory order for the appointment of a receiver is reviewable by the Supreme Court, a subsequent order made pending a writ of error in such case, supplying a vacancy in the office of receiver resulting from non-acceptance of the one first appointed, is not reviewable upon a fast writ of error. April 9, 1894.

Argued at the last term.

J. H. Lumpkin and Little, Wimbish & Worrill, for plaintiff in error. Blandeord & Grimes and Thornton & McMichael, contra.

Writ of error dismissed.
